  "_comment": "Full Modrinth pack manifest for build-mrpack. `mods` pins each mod to its exact tested build via `filename` (resolved to a Modrinth download link + sha1/sha512/size); an entry with no `filename` resolves by `version` (or the newest build for `minecraft` if version is null). `resourcepacks`/`shaderpacks`/`datapacks` are pulled from Modrinth too — their loader is minecraft/iris/datapack, not fabric, so the builder relaxes the loader filter for them. Datapacks land in each bundled world's datapacks/, so they need `build-mrpack --with-map`. AllTheMons is a combined resource-pack + datapack .zip, so it is listed in BOTH `resourcepacks` (client models) and `datapacks` (species data). Nothing here redistributes a jar/zip.",
